This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the analysis of PET images for the early diagnosis of Alzheimer's Disease. It also involves the use of deep learning techniques for image analysis. The paper also involves machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques for the analysis of PET images. Additionally, the paper involves the use of neural networks (cs.NE) for feature extraction and hierarchical graph clustering for pooling operations. Finally, the paper also involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC) as it deals with the diagnosis of a disease that affects humans.
